<item>
            <title>[HBASE-25050] We initialize Filesystems more than once.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-25050</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In HFileSystem&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// Create the &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;default&lt;/span&gt; filesystem with checksum verification switched on.
&lt;/span&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// By &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;default&lt;/span&gt;, any operation to &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt; FilterFileSystem occurs on
&lt;/span&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// the underlying filesystem that has checksums switched on.
&lt;/span&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.fs = FileSystem.get(conf);
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.useHBaseChecksum = useHBaseChecksum;

    fs.initialize(getDefaultUri(conf), conf);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We call fs.initialize(). Generally the FS would have been created and inited either in the FileSystem.get() call above or even when we try to check &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
  FileSystem fs = p.getFileSystem(c);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The FS that gets cached in the hadoop-common layer does the init for us. So we doing it again is redundant. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
